Attribution
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This is an independent, from-scratch port of the Bonsai Image inference pipeline
to the Qualcomm Hexagon NPU (QNN) for on-device (Android) use. It is not
affiliated with or endorsed by PrismML, Black Forest Labs, Alibaba Cloud,
Qualcomm, or Hugging Face.

Created using Bonsai Image by PrismML
  https://github.com/PrismML-Eng/Bonsai-Image-Demo  (Apache-2.0)

Bonsai Image is built from FLUX.2 [klein] 4B, Copyright 2026 Black Forest Labs
  https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.2-klein-4B  (Apache-2.0)

The text encoder is built from Qwen3-4B, Copyright 2024 Alibaba Cloud
  https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3-4B  (Apache-2.0)

The reference Python implementation this port was validated against is
mflux / mflux-prism, Copyright Filip Strand / PrismML  (MIT)

Dependencies:
  stable-diffusion.cpp, Copyright leejet  (MIT)
    The CPU text-encode and VAE-decode stages (sd-cli). The 1-bit Bonsai support
    comes from Juste-Leo2's fork (https://github.com/Juste-Leo2/stable-diffusion.cpp);
    our NPU-split hooks are added on top as a patch (see patches/).
  Qualcomm AI Engine Direct (QNN / QAIRT) SDK
    Used to run the diffusion transformer on the Hexagon NPU. Proprietary;
    obtain from Qualcomm under its own license. Not distributed here.

Model weights are NOT distributed with this repository. Download them from
PrismML under their own license (see README).
